                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d695">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1701A.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Consul at Cuidad Juarez</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-09T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1911—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department is informed that the Mexican consul at Juarez has reported to his
                    Government that in the course of the troubles of the last two days at Juarez
                    shots have been fired from the American side of the boundary.</p>
                <p>You will investigate and report by telegraph on these allegations; meanwhile, you
                    will promptly make telegraphic report upon the present situation and prospects
                    at Juarez.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
